text: Tricondyloides elongatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Tricondyloides elongatus. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It is 11 mm long and 2.5 mm wide, and its type locality is Plaine des Lacs, New Caledonia. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Tricondyloides elongatus
